Chinese scientists are warning that the country's northeast breadbasket regions are in danger of losing their fertility because of soil erosion and degeneration.
Soil erosion is deteriorating in northwest China's Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region as excessive herding and farming have outpaced the government's conservation efforts.
China would need 10 years to curb desertification that is exacerbating erosion around the world's highest and largest wetlands, the Sanjiangyuan Nature Reserve, have.
